   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_C0962_undated-03_page02.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                     <choice>
                        <orig>D<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi>
                        </orig>
                        <reg>Dear</reg>
                     </choice> Madam</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>You have brought trouble on<lb/>
               yourself by your cordial <choice>
                  <orig>man<lb/>
               ner</orig>
                  <reg>manner</reg>
               </choice> of desiring the pleasure<lb/>
               of doing commissions for me<lb/>
               in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Paris_FR">Paris</placeName>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               Besides 2 pairs of black<lb/>
               satin slippers (with strings)<lb/>
               I wish for a small gold<lb/>
               chain as nearly like that<lb/>
               which I enclose as you can<lb/>
               find without looking <hi rend="underline">far &amp;</hi>
               <lb/>
               <hi rend="underline">wide</hi>. - I gave this the other<lb/>
               day to a little child of a friend<lb/>
               and cannot replace it easily<lb/>
               in <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#London_ENK">London</placeName>. In <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Paris_FR">Paris</placeName> where<lb/>
               I bought this I know that<lb/>
               such chains are cheap <choice>
                  <orig>com<lb/>
               paratively</orig>
                  <reg>comparatively</reg>
               </choice> - Take the measure<lb/>
               of the length of this if you<lb/>
               please - A <hi rend="underline">French</hi> foot I believe<lb/>
               &amp; as well as I recollect it<lb/>
               did not cost above a <choice>
                  <orig>Napo-<lb/>
               leon</orig>
                  <reg>Napoleon</reg>
               </choice> - I take the liberty<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Princeton_C0962_undated-03_page03.jpg"/>
               of enclosing two sovereigns<lb/>
               well knowing from <choice>
                  <orig>expe<lb/>
               rience</orig>
                  <reg>experience</reg>
               </choice> that one has need<lb/>
               of all one's own money<lb/>
               during a visit to <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Paris_FR">Paris</placeName>
               <lb/>
               &amp; that it is a great <choice>
                  <orig>addi<lb/>
               tional</orig>
                  <reg>additional</reg>
               </choice> inconvenience to<lb/>
               have commissions to pay<lb/>
               for as well as to execute.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               My sister begs her <choice>
                  <orig>Compls</orig>
                  <reg>Compliments</reg>
               </choice>
               with mine to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HallX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Hall</persName>
            </p>
            <closer>
               I am D<hi rend="superscript">r.</hi> Madam<lb/>
               Yours sincerely<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>
                  The shoe which I send as<lb/>
                  a pattern fits exactly<lb/>
                  The new ones must not be <hi rend="underline">smaller</hi> especially in<lb/>
                  breadth otherwise I could<lb/>
                  not, at least I would not<lb/>
                  wear them -<lb/>
                  You understand that the chain<lb/>
                  I enclose must be returned<lb/>
                  by the bearer as it is no longer<lb/>
                  mine<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HallX2">Mr<hi rend="superscript">rs.</hi>Hall</persName>
                  </addrLine>
                  <addrLine>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Sloane-Street-59_FR">59 Sloane Street</placeName>
                  </addrLine>
               </address>
            </closer>
